Moving smoothly, Cody slid to the now twice-dead kobold. Lulu shifted as he did so, casting a wary eye at the far end of the
hall. Nudging the corpse aside with his foot, Cody uncovered the dart he had thrown, lying on the first step of the
staircase. "Good lurker, this one," Cody remarked, peering behind the stair. "We'll have to keep that in mind."
